1. Business Problem

Customer churn is a major challenge for subscription-based businesses such as telecom and internet service providers. When customers discontinue their services, companies lose recurring revenue and incur additional costs to acquire new customers.

The objective of this project is to build a machine learning model that predicts whether a customer is likely to churn based on their demographic and service-related information.

By identifying high-risk customers in advance, the company can implement targeted retention strategies to reduce churn and improve overall profitability.

📊 2. Project Objectives

Analyze customer behavior patterns.

Identify key factors influencing churn.

Build and evaluate classification models.

Deploy a prediction system for real-time churn risk detection.

Provide actionable business recommendations.

🎯 3. Success Metrics

We define both Technical Metrics and Business Metrics.

A. Technical Success Metrics

Since churn prediction is a classification problem, we will evaluate:

1️⃣ Accuracy

Overall percentage of correct predictions.

2️⃣ Precision

How many predicted churn customers actually churned.

3️⃣ Recall (VERY IMPORTANT)

How many actual churn customers were correctly identified.

👉 In churn problems, Recall is most important, because:
Missing a churn customer = lost revenue.

4️⃣ F1-Score

Balance between Precision and Recall.

5️⃣ ROC-AUC Score

Measures model’s ability to distinguish churn vs non-churn.

B. Business Success Metrics

Increase customer retention rate.

Reduce churn percentage.

Identify high-risk customers before contract expiration.

Estimate potential revenue at risk.

Enable targeted retention campaigns.

🧠 4. Expected Business Impact

If the company can identify even 60–70% of customers likely to churn, they can:

Offer discounts

Provide loyalty rewards

Improve service support

Increase long-term revenue

This results in:
✔ Reduced customer acquisition cost
✔ Increased lifetime value
✔ Improved profitability